President Biden visited FEMA headquarters to address the staff and provide an update on the response efforts to Hurricane Ian in Florida. He commended the coordination and efforts of the FEMA staff and other federal agencies involved in the response. The President expressed concern for the communities impacted by the hurricane and emphasized the need to provide immediate help and support. He announced that he had approved a major disaster declaration and signed the CREW Act into law, which provides job protection for FEMA reservists. The President also warned against price gouging by oil and gas companies and assured the people of Puerto Rico that the federal government is committed to their recovery. Secretary Mayorkas and Administrator Criswell also spoke, highlighting the ongoing efforts of the Department of Homeland Security and FEMA in supporting the affected areas. The President mentioned that he plans to meet with Governor DeSantis and visit Florida to personally thank the first responders and assess the situation.